{
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Until the spell ends, wind whirls around you, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Ranged weapon attacks made against you have disadvantage on the attack roll.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You gain a flying speed of 60 feet. If you are still flying when the spell ends, you fall, unless you can somehow prevent it.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You can use your action to create a 15-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} of swirling wind centered on a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in that area must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. A creature takes 2d10 &amp;Reference[bludgeoning]{bludgeoning} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If a Large or smaller creature fails the save, that creature is also pushed up to 10 feet away from the center of the &amp;Reference[cube]{cube}.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
